    <section ids="nfs-backup-driver" names="nfs\ backup\ driver">
        <title>NFS backup driver</title>
        <paragraph>The backup driver for the NFS back end backs up volumes of any type to
            an NFS exported backup repository.</paragraph>
        <paragraph>To enable the NFS backup driver, include the following option in the
            <literal>[DEFAULT]</literal> section of the <literal>cinder.conf</literal> file:</paragraph>
        <literal_block highlight_args="{}" language="ini" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">backup_driver = cinder.backup.drivers.nfs</literal_block>
        <paragraph>The following configuration options are available for the NFS back-end
            backup driver.</paragraph>
